The paper focuses on the application of Machine Learning algorithms for energy consumption forecasting, specifically Boosted Decision Tree Regression. This falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses feature engineering for time series forecasting, which falls under the category of Data Science (cs.DS). The authors also examine the methodology for creating personalised electricity plans, which falls under the category of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of smart meters, which can be considered a form of sensor networks, falling under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
